# simple cmake

1. without cmake

```cpp
// main.cpp
#include <iostream>

int main() {
  std::cout << "hello world\n";
}
```

`g++ -o main main.cpp`

2. with cmake

```bash

mkdir build && cd build

cmake ..

make

```

3. library target

4. a project example

credited to https://github.com/Yousif-CS/concurrency

https://www.youtube.com/live/AJRGU_XgVMQ?feature=share

install

```
cmake .. -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=(REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_ABSOLUTE_PATH)
```

to use in another project
```
cmake .. -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=(REPLACE_WITH_THE_ABOVE_PATH)
```
